{
  "text": "Like CD45, CD148 is a receptor-like PTP expressed in immune cells and a positive regulator of Src family kinases in B cells and macrophages [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . These redundant roles of CD148 and CD45 could therefore explain why no association was found between the potentially functional SNPs of CD148 analyzed in our study and the development of antibodies to H/PF4. Moreover, CD148 is present in platelets in larger amounts than CD45, which is marginally expressed in these blood cells [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "205409562",
